are neatly cut, with short serifs. P is open on both texts, R is closed. Text A has tall I in line three. The primary difference between Text A and Text B is in the technique, with the letters in A having a flat cut, whereas B is engraved with a more elegant 'v-cut' and more elegant interpuncts. It is likely that the two were carved by different stone-masons.",[284,288,292,296,300,304,308,311,314,317],{"type":34,"l":285,"from":286,"to":286,"h":287,"unit":37},"Line A 1","lineA1","37-39",{"type":34,"l":289,"from":290,"to":290,"h":291,"unit":37},"Line A 2","lineA2","32-35",{"type":34,"l":293,"from":294,"to":294,"h":295,"unit":37},"Line A 3","lineA3","27-33",{"type":34,"l":297,"from":298,"to":298,"h":299,"unit":37},"Line B 1","lineB1","35",{"type":34,"l":301,"from":302,"to":302,"h":303,"unit":37},"Line B 2","lineB2","30",{"type":34,"l":305,"from":306,"to":306,"h":307,"unit":37},"Line B 3","lineB3","27-29",{"type":39,"l":309,"from":286,"to":290,"h":310,"unit":37},"Interlineation line A1 to A2","12",{"type":39,"l":312,"from":290,"to":294,"h":313,"unit":37},"Interlineation line A2 to A3","11-13",{"type":39,"l":315,"from":298,"to":302,"h":316,"unit":37},"Interlineation line B1-B2","10",{"type":39,"l":318,"from":302,"to":306,"h":316,"unit":37},"Interlineation line B2-B3",{"_":320,"notBefore":321,"notAfter":322},"Perhaps between 16 BCE and 4 CE",-16,4,[324,325],{"_":48,"type":49,"ref":50},{"_":52,"type":53,"ref":54},[327],[57,58],{"_":62,"role":63,"ref":64},{"_":330,"type":331},"22522","inventory",{"_":333,"mainLang":334,"languages":335},"Latin","la",[333],{"n":70,"url":337,"height":72,"width":73,"desc":338,"surfaceType":75},"ISic003324A_tiled.tif","Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo Regionale Archeologico Pietro Griffo, Agrigento",[],[341,342,343,344,345,90,346],"De Miro, 1984-1985, L'attivita della soprintendenza archeologica di Agrigento (Anni 1980-84)","Manganaro, 1988, La Sicilia da Sesto Pompeo a Diocleziano","De Miro, 2000, Agrigento nella prima età imperiale","Pugliese Car